# Drishti-Link 👁️ — Real-Time Assistive Vision System

> **100% offline · privacy-first · agent-ready**
> Built for Google Antigravity · Production-grade Python

---

## Architecture

```
Mobile Camera (IP Webcam / MJPEG)
        │
        ▼
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│              DrishtiPipeline (Orchestrator)          │
│                                                     │
│  Thread A ──► frame_q ──► Thread B ──► result_q    │
│  FrameProducer            YOLOWorker    │           │
│  (cv2.VideoCapture)       YOLOv8n      │           │
│                           Spatial PQ   │           │
│                           Det. Memory  ▼           │
│                                   speech_q         │
│                                       │            │
│                                  Thread C          │
│                                  TTSConsumer       │
│                                  (pyttsx3)         │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘
        │ result_q
        ▼
 DrishtiDashboard (Tkinter)
 High-contrast Black/Neon-Yellow UI
```

## Quick Start

### 1 — Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 2 — Set up IP Webcam on Android
1. Install **IP Webcam** (Pavel Khlebovich) from the Play Store.
2. Start the server — note the URL shown (e.g. `http://192.168.1.100:8080`).
3. The video stream is at `http://192.168.1.100:8080/video`.

### 3 — Launch the dashboard
```bash
python dashboard.py
```
Enter your camera URL, press **▶ START VISION**.

### 4 — Headless / agent mode
```python
from main import DrishtiPipeline

pipe = DrishtiPipeline("http://192.168.1.100:8080/video")
pipe.start()

while True:
    pf = pipe.result_q.get()   # ProcessedFrame
    for det in pf.detections:
        print(det.label, det.priority, det.confidence)
```

---

## Key Design Decisions

| Feature | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Multi-threaded | Producer / Worker / TTS Consumer — separate threads, `queue.Queue` handoffs |
| Low latency | Frame queues capped at 2; oldest frame dropped when full |
| Spatial Priority Queue | `PRIORITY_MAP` dict — P1 (person/car) → P4 (bottle) |
| Detection Memory | Per-label `(timestamp, bbox_center)` — re-announce only after 5 s or >15% movement |
| Offline TTS | `pyttsx3` — zero network calls |
| YOLO model | `yolov8n.pt` auto-downloaded once, cached locally |
| UI | Tkinter — no external UI framework required; deep-black / neon-yellow WCAG AAA contrast |
| Heartbeat | ECG-style animated canvas — instant visual confirmation the pipeline is running |

---

## Extending for Google Antigravity Agents

`DrishtiPipeline` exposes three clean interfaces:

```python
pipe.result_q   # queue.Queue[ProcessedFrame]  — vision agent reads here
pipe.speech_q   # queue.Queue[str]             — agent can inject custom TTS
pipe.stop_evt   # threading.Event              — agent can stop the pipeline
```

Drop the pipeline into any agent loop with zero modification.

